author: Trefor Moss
title: Presidential Wannabes in Philippines Face Personal Tests
text:
MANILA—Three leading presidential contenders have emerged in the Philippines vowing to help the country keep its hard-won economic stride, but each faces formidable personal tests in this vibrant but sometimes chaotic democracy.
Corruption is expected to be a key theme for the May 2016 election—yet Vice President Jejomar Binay is trying to beat...
